Source code associated to the paper entitled "On securing online registration protocols: formal verification of a new proposal"
By Jesus Diaz, David Arroyo and Francisco B. Rodriguez
Tue Mar 13 09:32, 2012

Contents:
	* File "registration-ack.pv": Source code for ProVerif, in typed applied pi calculus, for the proposed protocol.
	  Run with ProVerif with: "proverif registration-ack.pv"
	* File "registration-ack-wo-ack.pv": Source code for ProVerif, in typed applied pi calculus, for the proposed
	  protocol, weakened by removing the ACK message. Run with "proverif registration-ack-wo-ack.pv"
	* File "registration-ack-wo-nonce.pv": Source code for ProVerif, in typed applied pi calculus, for the proposed
	  protocol, weakened by removing the nonce sent jointly with the SSL ticket. Run with 
	  "proverif registration-ack-wo-nonce.pv"
	* File "registration-ack-wo-ticket.pv": Source code for ProVerif, in typed applied pi calculus, for the proposed
	  protocol, weakened by removing the SSL ticket. Run with "proveif registration-ack-wo-ticket.pv"
	* File "saw.pv": Source code for ProVerif, in typed applied pi calculus, for the protocol proposed in 
	  "Simple Authentication for the Web". This code shows an attack on SAW, applicable also to the conventional
	  EBIA. Run with "proverif saw.pv".
	  
